.DAY ONE...TODAY AND TONIGHT

THUNDERSTORMS: ISOLATED TO SCATTERED THUNDERSTORMS ARE EXPECTED
OVER SOUTH FLORIDA THIS AFTERNOON. THE PRIMARY IMPACTS WILL BE GUSTY
WINDS, FREQUENT LIGHTNING STRIKES, AND LOCALLY HEAVY RAINFALL.

FLOODING: LOCALLY HEAVY RAINFALL IS POSSIBLE WITH ANY THUNDERSTORMS.
THEREFORE, THERE IS A SLIGHT RISK OF MINOR FLOODING OF ROADWAYS
AND LOW LYING AREAS TODAY.

TEMPERATURES: TODAY THE MAXIMUM TEMPERATURES WILL RANGE FROM THE
LOWER 90S ALONG THE COASTS TO THE MID-90S IN THE INTERIOR. THIS
WILL ELEVATE THE HEAT INDEX TO NEAR 105 DEGREES ACROSS MOST AREAS
TODAY, WITH ISOLATED AREAS IN THE INTERIOR POSSIBLY REACHING NEAR
110 DEGREES.

.DAYS TWO THROUGH SEVEN...FRIDAY THROUGH WEDNESDAY

SCATTERED SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS ARE POSSIBLE EACH DAY BUT MAINLY
DURING THE AFTERNOON AND EARLY EVENING.

